DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$pi = 3.141592654;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find the volume of the solid generated by revolving about the 
\(x\)-axis the region bounded by the upper half of the ellipse

\[ \dfrac{x^{2}}{a^{2}} + \dfrac{y^{2}}{b^{2}} = 1 \]

and the \(x\)-axis, and thus find the volume of a prolate
spheroid.  Here \(a\) and \(b\) are positive constants, with
\( a > b \).

$BR

Volume of the solid of revolution: \{ans_rule(10)\}.

EOT

$ans = "(4/3)*$pi*a*(b**2)";
ANS(fun_cmp($ans, limits=>[[0,1],[0,1]], vars=>["a","b"]));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
